caption: Table 1: Results of different single LVLM baselines.
description: This table presents the performance comparison of various single Large Vision-Language Models (LVLMs) on a geo-localization task, both with and without web search augmentation.  It shows the accuracy (Acc) achieved by each individual LVLM, broken down by image type (Natural and ManMade) and indicating whether web search was used. The table highlights the performance variation across different LVLMs, even within similar model sizes, and showcases the impact of leveraging web search capabilities.

caption: Table 2: Results of different agent frameworks without web searching.
description: This table compares the performance of various multi-agent frameworks for geo-localization without utilizing web search results.  It shows the accuracy (Acc) and average number of tokens (Tks) used per query for each framework.  The results highlight the impact of different collaborative strategies on accuracy and efficiency.

caption: Table 3: Comparison with image retrieval systems.
description: This table compares the performance of the proposed smileGeo framework against three state-of-the-art image retrieval baselines (NetVLAD, GeM, and CosPlace) on a geo-localization task.  The results show smileGeo's significantly higher accuracy in both natural and man-made landmark image geo-localization, highlighting its superior performance, particularly in open-world scenarios where the test data includes locations not present in the training data.

caption: Table 1: Results of different single LVLM baselines.
description: This table presents the performance comparison of different single Large Vision-Language Models (LVLMs) on visual geo-localization tasks.  It shows the accuracy achieved by each LVLM when used independently, both with and without web search capabilities, categorized by whether the location is natural or man-made. This helps to establish a baseline performance for comparison against multi-agent LVLMs and other geo-localization approaches.

caption: Table 1: Results of different single LVLM baselines.
description: This table compares the performance of various single Large Vision-Language Models (LVLMs) on a visual geo-localization task, both with and without the aid of web search.  The models are evaluated using the metrics of accuracy for natural and man-made landmarks, and overall accuracy. This provides a baseline for comparison against multi-agent LVLMs and image retrieval methods in later sections of the paper.
